# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  git-crypt — transparent encryption for the /private content tree
#
#  The markdown source files under src/private/content/ are encrypted at rest
#  using git-crypt. They look like plaintext locally (after `git-crypt unlock`)
#  but ship as binary blobs in the public repo.
#
#  Why bother? These are working notes — research, drafts, founder diligence,
#  deal templates, clinical/personal stuff. Not state secrets, but not the
#  kind of thing I want every casual passerby reading either.
#
#  If you're poking around because you find this stuff interesting:
#  reach out → chris@todie.io. I like talking to people who notice the gears.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

src/private/content/*.md filter=git-crypt diff=git-crypt
